short_description:
StrongKey CryptoEngine (SKCE) 2.0 is a FIDO-enabled (fidoalliance.org) web-service library that serves as a cryptographic engine to perform the following:

- FIDO U2F registrations/authentications;
- Encryption/Decryption using AES/TDES;
- Key-escrow/recovery to StrongAuth KeyAppliance (centralized key-manager);
- Digital signatures/verification; 
- LDAP  engine for AD/LDAP integration; and
- Cloud-storage integration to AWS S3, Azure and Eucalyptus Walrus.

It is intended for use with web-applications (see StrongKey CryptoCabinet on this site for a FOSS example application) to perform cryptographic functions through high-level web-services and free application developers to concentrate on business logic.

SKCE has been battle-tested and is in production at one of the largest e-commerce companies in the world, protecting more than 50M documents within the business process; see http://bit.ly/14VPYlO fpr the case-study.
